import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="State", y="Population", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set(xlabel='State', ylabel='Population')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across the states?', wrap=True)
    return plt

data = pd.read_csv('population_engineers_hurricanes.csv')
chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_csv('population_engineers_hurricanes.csv')

# Plot hurricanes by state
sns.set_style("whitegrid")
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.barplot(x='state', y='hurricanes', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
plt.title('What is the distribution of hurricanes across the states?')
plt.xlabel('State')
plt.ylabel('Number of hurricanes')
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.show()
